{
  "stem": "10588.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But when she came with a drama group-- in fact, I have even a picture that I retrieved from someone-- they got to know each other and obviously got married.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if-- but after my mother was married and she had a family, her priority was her home and her family.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so she would only perform for, for, tzedakah, for charity.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But she never lost the interest in the Yiddish theater.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she had a lovely voice.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And both my father and I used to sing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So what I remember a lot is how they used to sing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In fact, I can still remember my mother's feel, like my mother's cheek, like when she would put me to bed.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Or sometimes, my father would sing me Yiddish lullabies, Yiddish songs.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because in our home, even though both my parents and my grandmother could speak fluently Polish and Yiddish, we only spoke Yiddish at home.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So they taught me lots of Yiddish songs.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Another thing I remember about my father, he would always ask us, so what did you learn, my child?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Which made me aware that there is a lesson in every experience.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And also, I remember that we had-- I felt loved by my parents.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I felt that both my parents and my grandmother loved me unconditionally.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But, they also were strict with us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "From early childhood on, both my parents and my grandmother stressed to us the importance of menschlichkeit, which in the English language means humaneness.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Whenever I wouldn't do something which would measure up to the yardstick of menschlichkeit, they would always used to say, 'Itkele, it's not menschlich.' And that used to helped me more than if they would physically hit me, because I felt like I let them down.",
      "word_count": 46
    }
  ],
